      "amount": "1 teaspoon",
      "notes": "ground"
    },
    {
      "name": "cayenne pepper",
      "amount": "1/4 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "olive oil",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until it is softened and lightly browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the lamb and cook until it is browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, and cayenne pepper and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add 1 cup of water and bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.",
    "Stir in the crumbled manchego cheese and pitted dates.",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley or cilantro."
  ],
